name: Star Wars sith outfit
description:
Ok, this one was requested a lot.

UPDATE, MADE V2:

Changed trigger word, as the first version was using too much of the existing trigger word in the models and the results were not very consistent.

Trigger word is sthoutfit (without the i).

This version works best at 1.0 strength

This version does not have big problem with face paint or lightsabres, but as with the previous one you can supress it with negative prompting.

You will see that there is no Anakins outfit in this LORA. I tired to use it in one of the first versions, but this is what i got:

For me those are jedi, not sith, that is why i got rid of this outfit in the data set.

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description: Changed trigger word to not use the one that was already recognized by the model
